# pocketforge-foreground.target — the exclusive foreground display-app slot.
#
# THE SEAM (tsp-ikk0.11, design ruled by tsp-3rd3-coord 2026-07-16): any app
# that takes the panel joins this target DECLARATIVELY — no per-app
# animator-kill hardcoding anywhere. An app unit (or a `pf-take-panel`
# transient unit) declares:
#
#     [Unit]
#     Requires=pocketforge-foreground.target
#     After=pocketforge-foreground.target
#
# Starting the app then:
#   1. activates this target, whose activation — via the animator's
#      Conflicts=/Before= on it — first STOPS pocketforge-boot-animator
#      (SIGTERM → clears fb0 to black → exit 0, the tsp-3rd3.4 contract),
#   2. and only then starts the app (After= orders it behind the stop),
#      so fb0 has exactly ONE writer at all times. This kills the
#      splash/app pan-fight on the double-buffered fb0 that the owner saw
#      as "z-fighting" (root cause proven in bead tsp-7kpp).
#
# StopWhenUnneeded: when the last joined app unit exits, the target
# deactivates on its own; OnSuccess then restores the boot animator, so the
# device returns to its splash steady-state. A brief black flash during
# handoff is ACCEPTED by design ruling — seamless splash→app handoff is
# deferred to tsp-3rd3.4.
#
# KNOWN FUTURE EDGE (for tsp-y2di, the launcher milestone): OnSuccess
# restores the animator unconditionally. When a persistent MainUI ships
# (owning the panel via pocketforge-splash-handoff.target), a game exiting
# this slot would wrongly revive the animator over the MainUI — the
# launcher integration must define that interaction (e.g. the launcher
# itself joins this target persistently, or replaces the OnSuccess=). Do
# not "fix" it here pre-launcher.
#
# bd: tsp-ikk0.11 (root cause: tsp-7kpp; design intent: tsp-3rd3.4)

[Unit]
Description=PocketForge foreground display-app slot (exclusive fb0 ownership)
Documentation=https://github.com/pocketforge-os/image/tree/main/apps/pocketforge-boot-animator
DefaultDependencies=no
StopWhenUnneeded=yes
OnSuccess=pocketforge-boot-animator.service
Conflicts=shutdown.target
Before=shutdown.target
